    "text": "RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) is a powerful technique in AI.\nIt combines retrieval of relevant documents with generative language models.\nThis system uses Sentence-BERT for embeddings and FAISS for fast vector search.\nChunking documents into smaller overlapping pieces improves retrieval accuracy.\nGoogle Gemini or Claude 3.5 Sonnet can be used as the answering LLM.\n\nVector embeddings convert text into high-dimensional vectors so that similar meanings are close together in vector space.",
